        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "hornc@cray.com",
          "date": "2019-06-10 15:46:55.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-12410 lnet: Fix lnetctl peer add/del nid parsing",
        "message": "LU-12410 lnet: Fix lnetctl peer add/del nid parsing\n\nThe arguments to lnetctl peer add/del --prim_nid and --nid options\nare currently treated as ip2net expressions. This prevents us from\ndefining peers with NIs that do not use ip addresses (currently just\ngnilnd). Add a proper code path for handling nids rather than ip2net\nexpressions. Add a more informative error message when un-supported\nnet types are specified in an ip2net expression.\n\nTest-parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ie099410bb677e1c698b6b5d939eb5e9e246db29a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
